<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="V" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Violate" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Violate,</orth> to sin against; to break (a vow etc.), to dishonour, to do violence to (maiden honour): <cit><quote>makest the vestal v. her oath,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 883" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 883</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--d troth,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 883" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 883</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 71</bibl>. <cit><quote>to v. the honour of my child,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.347" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 347</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.284" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 284</bibl>. <cit><quote>experience, manhood, honour, ne'er before did v. so itself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.10.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 10, 24</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>